verbose_text: Elevated levels of inflammatory biomarkers such as C-reactive protein (CRP), interleukin (IL) 6 and 18, fibrinogen, and adhesion molecules (e.g., E-selectin, intercellular adhesion molecule 1 (ICAM-1), and vascular cell adhesion protein 1 (VCAM-1) sustain evidence of a central role of inflammation in CVD, type 2 diabetes or cancer.
